summary: The diff implements a centralized React Query dashboard export query (with a stable queryKey), updates DashboardPage and BenchDocumentsEditor to consume it, and indicates that document/bench-document mutations now invalidate the dashboard export query for instant refresh. There are also unrelated changes in BenchDetailPage (component duplicate detection / other refactoring) not requested by the BuildRequest.

hallucinated_features.description: Added client-side duplicate detection logic when saving bench components (blocking save and showing an error toast).
hallucinated_features.reason: The BuildRequest is specifically about dashboard documents refreshing after bench-document changes; it does not request new validation rules or UX changes for bench components saving.

hallucinated_features.description: Bench detail page refactor/behavior changes unrelated to document refresh (e.g., hooks/import changes such as using useGetComponents instead of another hook, additional localized UI behavior).
hallucinated_features.reason: These changes are not part of REQ-1..REQ-4 and go beyond fixing the dashboard documents refresh behavior.
